nn profiles more than two dozen organizations ranging from child-care cooperatives to retirement communities, from co-housing "villages" to financial institutions. He also investigates public-policy changes that could strengthen this alternative sector's contribution to economic development.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aCooperationzUnited States. 0aHuman serviceszUnited States. 0aNon-governmental organizationszUnited States. 0aNonprofit organizationszUnited States. 4aBusiness (General). 4aGeneral Economics. 4aPublic Policy.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013z978311053615740uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150172533340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501725333423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501725333/original  a978-3-11-053615-7  Cornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles